Gatara::

"We were chasing a small shuttlecraft that passed too close to where 
we were working.  That operation is now lost to us, as Rogue Star got 
caught in a space-time rip and flung to Earth's distant past."  
Gatara turns to the console nearest her, and examines the read-out.  
"We were in the process of repairing the ship when Jayde's scouting 
mission went awry.  Devilcat, Riekan, and Torin went to rescue her - 
we're keeping watch here.  Everyone else is in stasis lock because of 
the energy storm that sent us down."

--- In nbwrpg@y..., "x_rauq_x" <x_rauq_x@y...> wrote:
> -- Noir --
> 
> Noir's optics focus on Gatara, and she nods her aknowledgement at 
> the bot. The rather large Rogue named Gatara was known to her, and 
> her memories to be a formidable ally, and not one to be trifled 
with.
> 
> "Some living, some are already dead." She pauses, the continues 
> before Gatara can say anything, "Where is Devilcat, and what is the 
> Rogues current situation on wherever it is we have landed. 
> Unfortunately my memory has a few blanks still, and I can not 
> remember our final destination."
